					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">- Like I said, unless there's a good timestamp system for PPU/APU/whatver read/write, cpuexec(cycles) is a waste. Assuming only NTSC will be emulated, yes, 1 NTSC CPU cycle = 3 PPU cycles.
<br />
<br />- In my emulator, that means for each CPU cycle, the PPU burns 3 cycles, meaning 3 dots. On other hand, as blargg have mentioned, it's better to have something working good firstly.</div>

